events.name: IWD Banjul 2018
events.description:
• What we'll do
We are proud to be hosting the 2018 International Women's Day Celebration, a women's tech conference. This event will highlight the stories of our growing female community of designers, developers, and technology entrepreneurs.

• What to bring
Please bring a Laptop! if you don't have one that's okay too :)

Agenda:
10:00-10:30
Registration
10:30-10:40
Welcoming Remarks
10:40-11:10
Ice Breakers
11:10-12:10
Experience sharing,Panel discussion / Q&A session
12:10-13:10
Protecting yourself online
13:10-14:00
Lunch Break
14:00-16:00
Codelabs Session - Build your first Android app in Java
16:00
Closing Remarks/ Networking

events.name: Jokkolabs International Women's Day Celebrations
events.description:
As part of the International Women’s Day celebrations, Jokkolabs Banjul we will be hosting “Be Bold for Change” on Thursday, March 7th 2019 starting at 10:00am, in collaboration with GDG Banjul and SHOAW Gambia, an initiative that seeks to address the increasing harassment and online abuse of women and girls in The Gambia. The event shall take place in Jokkolabs Banjul at the YMCAs Computer Training Centre and Digital Studio, opposite MDI.

This event will focus on the online and in person harassment of girls in the community. We have invited local community organizations that focus on empowering women and girls to speak about what they do, how girls can get involved, and the resources available to them. Following the showcase, we will have a group discussion around questions that the girls may have around harassment in the community. Finally, we will have a breakout session with all the students to help create lists of what they can do to keep themselves safe both online and in person, each group will share their list in a short presentation with the larger group.
events.how_to_find_us: We're located in the YMCA building, opposite MDI, in Kanifing South.

events.name: Next '19 Extended Banjul
events.description:
Join us at our Google Cloud Next extended event, as we celebrate and retrace the highlights of the google cloud next ’19 event (https://cloudnext.withgoogle.com/) that will be held form April 9th to 11th in San Francisco. We also plan to have a Study Jam, live Demos from local Tech companies and a surprise contest!
More details coming soon.

Please Register to save your place.
events.how_to_find_us: We will be in Jokkolabs space in the YMCA building opposite MDI.

events.name: Flutter Interact: Viewing Party
events.description:
Flutter is an open-source mobile application development framework created by Google. This year, flutter, Google’s latest innovation for mobile, web, and desktop apps will be hosting a major event "Flutter Interact", on December 11th 2019, to announce new technologies associated with Flutter.
We would love for you to join us for a viewing party on December 17th, to watch a Keynote and have a Codelabs activity session. Please bring a laptop for this portion of the event. We will have lots of surprises including a free coupon for a Flutter course.

To participate in this event, there is a fee of 100 dalasis.
events.how_to_find_us: We are directly opposite MDI in Kanifing South.

upcoming.name: Firebase Study Jam
upcoming.description:
Want to get started building web apps? Learn how to do that with Firebase!
Join us for our Firebase Study Jam! Together we'll work through Firebase for web codelabs prepared by Google instructors and get some hands-on experience with Firebase.
Please bring a laptop and don't forget your charger!
